  <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\08_Functional_Timing\Topics\SPI_slave_interface_prg.xml" xtrc="title:1;3:10">SPI Slave Interface for Programming Configuration</title>

  <body class="- topic/body " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\08_Functional_Timing\Topics\SPI_slave_interface_prg.xml" xtrc="body:1;5:9">
    <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\08_Functional_Timing\Topics\SPI_slave_interface_prg.xml" xtrc="p:1;6:8">The device provides a SPI slave interface for programming the external
    flash device as noted in <xref href="../../../Other/SPI_Slave_Flash_Programming_Interface_fiu913pm6.xml#SPI_Slave_Flash_Programming_Interface_fiu913pm6/SPI_Flash_Programming_Solution_giu913pm6" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\08_Functional_Timing\Topics\SPI_slave_interface_prg.xml" xtrc="xref:1;7:200" type="fig"><?ditaot gentext?>Figure 1</xref>.
    The flash content to be programmed is available from the company website.
    The slave interface must be enabled and flash device programmed using the
    following sequence.</p>

    <ol class="- topic/ol " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\08_Functional_Timing\Topics\SPI_slave_interface_prg.xml" xtrc="ol:1;12:9">
      <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\08_Functional_Timing\Topics\SPI_slave_interface_prg.xml" xtrc="li:1;13:11"><p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\08_Functional_Timing\Topics\SPI_slave_interface_prg.xml" xtrc="p:2;13:14"> Assert device RSTB=0</p></li>

      <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\08_Functional_Timing\Topics\SPI_slave_interface_prg.xml" xtrc="li:2;15:11"><p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\08_Functional_Timing\Topics\SPI_slave_interface_prg.xml" xtrc="p:3;15:14"> Assert SPI_SLV2MST_EN=1</p></li>

      <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\08_Functional_Timing\Topics\SPI_slave_interface_prg.xml" xtrc="li:3;17:11"><p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\08_Functional_Timing\Topics\SPI_slave_interface_prg.xml" xtrc="p:4;17:14"> Apply extended SPI single-IO mode command sequences on the SPI
      Slave Interface For Programming Configuration (SPI_SLV_PRG_SCLK,
      SPI_SLV_PRG_SSB, SPI_SLV_PRG_MOSI, SPI_SLV_PRG_MISO) that conforms to
      the functional timing of <xref href="#xd_61ce80ebee13fc16--385ca96f-157be33a17a--7c00/fig_SPI_Slave_Interface_for_Programming_Conf_2iui2yvba" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\08_Functional_Timing\Topics\SPI_slave_interface_prg.xml" xtrc="xref:2;20:149" type="fig"><?ditaot gentext?>Figure 2</xref> and <xref href="#xd_61ce80ebee13fc16--385ca96f-157be33a17a--7c00/fig_SPI_Slave_Interface_for_Programming_Conf_3iui2yvbb" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\08_Functional_Timing\Topics\SPI_slave_interface_prg.xml" xtrc="xref:3;21:136" type="fig"><?ditaot gentext?>Figure 1</xref> from an external master device to:</p><ul class="- topic/ul " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\08_Functional_Timing\Topics\SPI_slave_interface_prg.xml" xtrc="ul:1;22:57">
          <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\08_Functional_Timing\Topics\SPI_slave_interface_prg.xml" xtrc="li:4;23:15"><p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\08_Functional_Timing\Topics\SPI_slave_interface_prg.xml" xtrc="p:5;23:18">Perform initial configuration of the SPI Flash device
          non-volatile configuration register fields as required for the SPI
          flash device to interoperate with the DIGI-G5 boot mode SPI memory
          read commands.</p></li>

          <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\08_Functional_Timing\Topics\SPI_slave_interface_prg.xml" xtrc="li:5;28:15"><p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\08_Functional_Timing\Topics\SPI_slave_interface_prg.xml" xtrc="p:6;28:18">Erase flash memory.</p></li>

          <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\08_Functional_Timing\Topics\SPI_slave_interface_prg.xml" xtrc="li:6;30:15"><p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\08_Functional_Timing\Topics\SPI_slave_interface_prg.xml" xtrc="p:7;30:18">Program flash memory with boot code image.</p></li>
        </ul></li>

      <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\08_Functional_Timing\Topics\SPI_slave_interface_prg.xml" xtrc="li:7;33:11"><p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\08_Functional_Timing\Topics\SPI_slave_interface_prg.xml" xtrc="p:8;33:14"> De-assert SPI_SLV2MST_EN=0</p></li>

      <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\08_Functional_Timing\Topics\SPI_slave_interface_prg.xml" xtrc="li:8;35:11"><p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\08_Functional_Timing\Topics\SPI_slave_interface_prg.xml" xtrc="p:9;35:14"> Upon de-asserting device RSTB=0, DIGI-G5 will proceed with
      device boot and read from the SPI flash device</p></li>
    </ol>

    <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\digi\Chapters\08_Functional_Timing\Topics\SPI_slave_interface_prg.xml" xtrc="p:10;39:8">The SPI slave flash programming interface supports only single-IO mode
    4-wire SPI. The following figures shown typical single-IO mode read and
    page program command sequences over the SPI slave flash programming
    interface. The address phase may contain 3 or 4 bytes, or be absent,
    depending on the command in use and mode of operation of the flash device.
    The data phase may be absent depending on the command in use.</p>

